## Ingredients

### Chickpeas

- [ ] 1 cup dried chickpeas, soaked overnight (or 2x 15 oz cans, drained)
- [ ] 2.5 cups water (if using dried chickpeas)

### Sauce Base

- [ ] 1 Tbsp ghee or oil
- [ ] 1 tsp cumin seeds
- [ ] 1 large onion, finely diced
- [ ] 1 Tbsp minced ginger
- [ ] 4 cloves garlic, minced
- [ ] 1 green chili, minced (or 1/4 tsp cayenne pepper)
- [ ] 2 medium tomatoes, chopped (or 1 cup crushed tomatoes)
- [ ] 2 tsp chana masala spice blend (or substitute: 1 tsp garam masala + 1/2 tsp ground coriander + 1/2 tsp ground cumin)
- [ ] 1 tsp ground coriander
- [ ] 1/2 tsp turmeric powder
- [ ] 1/2 tsp red chili powder (adjust to taste)
- [ ] 1 tsp salt

### Finishing

- [ ] 1 Tbsp lemon juice (or 1 tsp amchoor/dried mango powder)
- [ ] 1/2 tsp garam masala
- [ ] Fresh cilantro, chopped (for garnish)

### For Serving

- [ ] Basmati rice or naan bread

## Recipe

1. If using dried chickpeas, soak overnight in plenty of water; drain before using. For canned chickpeas, skip to step 4
1. Add soaked chickpeas and 2.5 cups water to Instant Pot
1. Close lid and cook on high pressure for 15-20 minutes; allow natural pressure release for 10 minutes, then quick release remaining pressure
1. Open lid and drain excess liquid, reserving 1 cup of cooking liquid
1. Set Instant Pot to saut√© mode and heat ghee or oil
1. Add cumin seeds and let sizzle for 30 seconds until fragrant
1. Add diced onion and cook until softened and golden, about 5-7 minutes
1. Add ginger, garlic, and green chili; cook for 1 minute until fragrant
1. Add chopped tomatoes and cook until softened, about 3-4 minutes
1. Add chana masala spice blend, coriander, turmeric, chili powder, and salt; stir and cook for 1 minute
1. Return cooked chickpeas to pot with 1/2-1 cup of reserved cooking liquid
1. Use back of spoon or potato masher to lightly mash some chickpeas to thicken sauce
1. Simmer for 5-10 minutes until sauce thickens and chickpeas are well-coated
1. Turn off heat and stir in lemon juice and garam masala
1. Serve garnished with fresh cilantro, alongside rice or naan

## Notes

- Serves 4
- Total time: 50 minutes (30 min for chickpeas + 20 min for sauce) plus overnight soaking
- For quick soak: Cover dried chickpeas with boiling water and soak 2 hours
- Using canned chickpeas reduces cook time to 20 minutes
- Vegetarian and can easily be made vegan by using oil instead of ghee
- High in protein (11g per serving) and fiber (14g per serving)
- Nutrition per serving: 260 calories, 34g carbs
- Chana masala spice blend is available at most US grocery stores in the international aisle
- The slight tanginess from lemon juice or amchoor is essential to authentic flavor
